RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 51000. (UP TO $9,000 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $65,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACKERET was off a half beat slower than any other, got asked early but was slow to settle into stride, began to pick up the pace nearing the end of the backstretch, tipped into the three path at the top of the turn and patiently kept watch on the front runners, got set down challenging them in earnest four wide heading home, poked a head down in front at the start of the final furlong, drew off, kept to urging to the end. WHATEVERYOUWANT pressed the issue from the three path, shook free of the fellow front runners as the half was being completed, got set down for the drive, lost the advantage by the end of the run through the furlong grounds, held on well though to secure second. JET ALLEY appeared headstrong racing down the backstretch, requiring the pilot to steady the mount along, departed the backstretch from the four path, made his presence felt forcing the pace, lacked the necessary stretch response and had to settle for the show. RICHIE'S RICH darted over to the rail after the start, tracked the pace to the quarter pole before backing away. HUMBOLT STREET ducked in awkwardly, bumping lightly with RADAMEL, went on to save ground to no avail. RADAMEL bumped lightly with HUMBOLT STREET after being released from the gate, prompted the pacesetter from the three path, between rivals for the majority of the time, lost speed abruptly nearing the five-sixteenths marker, got eased, walked off.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners of two races since February 1 Allowed 2 lbs. A race since then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000. (If the Stewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at Seven Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 27 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERING GALE three to two wide racing around the turn, was put to solid encouragement taking the four path for entrance into the stretch, gained ground readily during the ensuing furlong, was beaten to the lead by the runner up, but just barely at the eighth pole, got hooked in a spirited tussle with that opponent the rest of the way to the wire, cemented herself to the front in the final seventy yards and inched away. SIMPLE LOVE took up position in the pocket, was pulling on the bit for the majority of the way down the backstretch, cut the corner into the stretch with sufficient clearance along the inside corridor to launch a rally and did so, slipped by the front runners approaching the furlong marker to attain a slim lead, was forced to fend off the eventual winner, battled on with good determination but came up short. LIL HONEY BADGER got guided over to the rail shortly after the start, had the pilot increase his grip on the reins and got taken back about a body length's worth of distance nearing the end of the backstretch, proceeded to gradually angle into the three path from that juncture to the five-sixteenths pole, was put to strong urging turning for home two paths wider, finished with willingness to secure the show. NONNIE CONNIE bobbled at the start, yet out-broke the field by the narrowest of margins, stalked the pacesetter from the two path to the quarter pole then backed away. SPANISH CONCERT made a quick move over to the rail after the start, showed the way on a loosely-contested lead to the quarter pole, got set down for the drive, drifted towards the two path a couple of jumps later, yielded to heavy pressure a short distance from the eighth pole and faltered. RADIANT CUT took up the chase in the two path, failed to menace. BLISSTERING STRIKE underwent a three wide pursuit on the turn before giving away.

HORATIO dueled lightly coaxed just off the inside with GLORY GAME to his outside, drifted three wide midway on the turn, spun just off the inside for home under threat from new rivals, got headed near the three-sixteenths and weakened. GLORY GAME lightly coaxed three wide dueling with the aforementioned foe, floated four wide as that rival drifted out midway on the turn, swung three wide into upper stretch and tired. STAR OF NEW YORK squeezed between foes and bumped both sides at the start, chased three to four wide under urging from the five-sixteenths, angled five to six wide into upper stretch and made no impact. EVERYDOGHASHISDAY chased the pace inside forwardly placed early on, retreated through the turn and tired.

PERFECT FREUD two to three wide in pursuit forwardly placed, got put to encouragement three furlongs out, spun three wide for home, weakened in the drive. SARATIAGO lunged at the start getting off half a beat slow, chased three wide from towards the rear a bit green and erratic early on requiring the rider to tap the off side with the stick, came under a ride midway on the turn, swung three to four wide for home, made no impact. YELLOW CELLO bumped at the start by MISS MATZOBALL who broke inwards, saved ground towards the rear, came under encouragement three furlongs from home, angled five wide into upper stretch, made no impact. JESSAMINE just off the inside towards the rear, got pushed along from the three-eighths pole, never threatened.
